# Project structure and technology stack

- **Main project:** escapezoom_wp-dev (this workspace). **Reference project:** escapezoom_wp. Use it for structure, patterns, and conventions; align with it when relevant.
- **Prefer professional, off-the-shelf packages and libraries.** Build custom solutions only when there is no good existing option. In 99% of cases do not reinvent the wheel.

## mu-plugins — escapezoom-core (mandatory)

The technology stack and structure for **escapezoom-core** are **mandatory**. See **rule 16 (16-muplugin-stack-mandatory.mdc)** for the required PHP version, Composer packages (Carbon Fields, Corcel, Illuminate database/cache/validation/events/queue/support/contracts, Guzzle when needed), and mandatory directory layout (PSR-4, src/Core/, src/Database/, src/Modules/ with Models/Services/Repositories, src/API/, src/Helpers/). Implementations MUST comply with rule 16; do not use "prefer" or "should" for the core stack — it is required.

## Theme escapezoom-v3 (mandatory)

The technology stack and structure for **escapezoom-v3** are **mandatory**. See **rule 17 (17-theme-stack-mandatory.mdc)** for the required npm package manager, Vite/Stencil/Tailwind build, mandatory scripts (dev, build, build:vite, css:build), front-end stack (Alpine.js, Embla Carousel with autoplay/fade, Flatpickr, htmx, jalaali-js), and mandatory structure (assets/js, assets/css, assets/vendor; template/ and app/). Implementations MUST comply with rule 17; do not use "prefer" or "should" for the theme stack — it is required.
